GENERAL SUMMARY
Teacher U is a revolutionary[co] practical[co] results-oriented teacher training program developed by the founders of Uncommon Schools[co] KIPP[co] and Achievement First. Over the past three years[co] Teacher U has managed a master[ap]s level program at Hunter College and recently has created a new[co] independent graduate program[co] Relay School of Education[co] which will begin operations in the summer of 2011.
The Director of Research will play an integral role in this new graduate school of education by helping to design and manage this new institution[ap]s research agenda. Built on a tradition of data-driven decision making[co] Relay School of Education must be positioned to answer two key research questions:
Are graduates of our program significantly better at leading K-12 students to achievement gains than graduates of other teacher training programs?
What are the knowledge[co] skills[co] and mindset that new teachers must learn to be exceptionally effective at improving student growth and achievement?
In short[co] this is an outstanding opportunity to play a significant role in urban[co] public education reform by helping to define and answer questions about new teacher training and effectiveness.
ESSENTIAL DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES
Define the Relay Research Agenda and Present Findings Associated with that Agenda&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Work with the Relay[ap]s President and Provost to craft an ambitious institution-wide research agenda; and
Present findings associated with the research agenda in publications[co] to external organizations[co] and at conferences.
Design and Manage Internal Data Collection Systems&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Determine what data the institution needs to collect retroactively and in the future;
Collaborate with the Provost and Dean[co] to intentionally build data capture into the program design and implementation; and
Collaborate with the Knowledge Management and Technology teams to implement systems and processes for data capture and analysis.
Work with Internal Teammates to Solve Methodological Challenges and to Conduct Meaningful Analysis and Research
Work with the Provost and Instructional Design Team to solve methodological challenges (e.g. best ways to hold teachers accountable for student growth and achievement);
Analyze internal data to help inform curricular design and implementation;
Manage part-time data manager;
Work with Relay Professors to shape research projects that meaningfully contribute to answering the larger institutional research agenda; and
Serve as an in-house resource for faculty members as they have methodological questions or challenges when conducting their own research.
Work with External Research Partners
Manage large-scale external program evaluations of Relay School of Education (e.g. a study by Mathematica);
Work with like-minded organizations (e.g. TFA[co] TNTP[co] Boston Teacher Residency[co] etc¡­) to share data[co] findings[co] and best practices; and
Field[co] vet[co] and manage any research requests from external researchers (e.g. doctoral students interested in studying Relay).
QUALIFICATIONS
First and foremost[co] the Director of Research must share the team[ap]s sense of urgency about the need to improve student achievement through phenomenal teacher preparation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally[co] candidates for the position must possess the following:
Earned doctorate in a relevant field (e.g. Applied Statistics[co] Educational Measurement[co] Quantitative Policy Analysis in Education[co] etc¡­) required;
Fluency in at least one statistical software package (e.g. Stata[co] SAS[co] SPSS[co] etc¡­);
Excellent written and verbal communication skills for both technical and non-technical audiences;
Excellent organization and project management skills;
Sophisticated interpersonal skills including the ability to work with and manage a broad range of constituents;
Proven mastery of teaching[co] with measurable evidence of driving student achievement gains[co] in high©\need[co] K©\12 public schools¡ªpreferred;
Demonstrated passion for urban education and closing the achievement gap; and
High level of zest[co] grit[co] hope[co] gratitude[co] and humor.
